        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1646431057" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1423230542903623014"><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10291971.In_the_Sea_There_are_Crocodiles_Based_on_the_True_Story_of_Enaiatollah_Akbari' title='In the Sea There are Crocodiles Based on the True Story of Enaiatollah Akbari by Fabio Geda' rel='nofollow noopener'>In the Sea There are Crocodiles: Based on the True Story of Enaiatollah Akbari</a>, is a short but fascinating story of a ten year old Afghanistan boy&apos;s journey from Pakistan to Italy. He was brought to Pakistan by his mother because she feared for his life in Afghanistan. She was unable to stay there with him as she had younger children still in Afghanistan which relied on her, so she gave Akbari the advice which she hoped would lead to his survival.<br/><br/>Akbari was indeed a very resilient child who surv</span>
  <span id="freeText1423230542903623014" style="display:none"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10291971.In_the_Sea_There_are_Crocodiles_Based_on_the_True_Story_of_Enaiatollah_Akbari" title="In the Sea There are Crocodiles Based on the True Story of Enaiatollah Akbari by Fabio Geda" rel="nofollow noopener">In the Sea There are Crocodiles: Based on the True Story of Enaiatollah Akbari</a>, is a short but fascinating story of a ten year old Afghanistan boy's journey from Pakistan to Italy. He was brought to Pakistan by his mother because she feared for his life in Afghanistan. She was unable to stay there with him as she had younger children still in Afghanistan which relied on her, so she gave Akbari the advice which she hoped would lead to his survival.<br /><br />Akbari was indeed a very resilient child who survived dark and dismal times. He traveled over the years from Pakistan to Iran and then into Turkey. From Turkey he traveled across the treacherous stretch of the Mediterranean Sea to Greece. <br /><br />His an incredible story and worth reading. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1423230542903623014" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
