<div id="review_195987243" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/195987243" />
    <a title="Barb" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/849475-barb"><img alt="Barb" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1241270439p2/849475.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/195987243?book_show_action=true">Aug 08, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Barb" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Barb" href="/user/show/849475-barb">Barb</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/849475-barb?shelf=read-in-2011">read-in-2011</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/849475-barb?shelf=vine">vine</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/849475-barb?shelf=fictionz-of-real-people">fictionz-of-real-people</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/849475-barb?shelf=new-in-2011">new-in-2011</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/849475-barb?shelf=memoirs">memoirs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer195987243" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11734271530361702672">I was moved by Enaiatollah Akbari&apos;s story, I&apos;m glad that Fabio Geda has recorded it for the sake of history but I wish that Geda had expanded on the details a little more or that I had read this with a companion book on Afghanistan so that I would have had a greater understanding of what daily life was like for Akbari there. <br/><br/>I thought this was a moving story but lacked the details that would have made it a richer reading experience for me. I think it would be an excellent book for the right teac</span>
  <span id="freeText11734271530361702672" style="display:none">I was moved by Enaiatollah Akbari's story, I'm glad that Fabio Geda has recorded it for the sake of history but I wish that Geda had expanded on the details a little more or that I had read this with a companion book on Afghanistan so that I would have had a greater understanding of what daily life was like for Akbari there. <br /><br />I thought this was a moving story but lacked the details that would have made it a richer reading experience for me. I think it would be an excellent book for the right teacher to use with her students when teaching them about Afghanistan and the Middle East. It feels as if this was intended for the YA audience and that may be part of why I didn't enjoy it more.<br /><br />I wish Enaiatollah Akbari success and happiness in all he does.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11734271530361702672" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
