<div id="review_2107965823" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2107965823" />
    <a title="Carole" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4708829-carole"><img alt="Carole" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1400514087p2/4708829.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2107965823?book_show_action=true">Aug 29, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carole" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carole" href="/user/show/4708829-carole">Carole</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4708829-carole?shelf=immigrant-literature">immigrant-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4708829-carole?shelf=biography">biography</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2107965823" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15957190400644430803">This book is based on the recollections of a refugee, a young man whose mother took him to Pakistan, from their home in Afghanistan, and abandoned him at age 10, without warning, so he might have a brighter future. What a struggle this youngster experienced. Through luck and ingenuity he was able to survive and eventually sneak into Iran, where he could make a subsistence, along with a number of other illegal workers, in construction. He was constantly in danger of deportation back to Pakistan, </span>
  <span id="freeText15957190400644430803" style="display:none">This book is based on the recollections of a refugee, a young man whose mother took him to Pakistan, from their home in Afghanistan, and abandoned him at age 10, without warning, so he might have a brighter future. What a struggle this youngster experienced. Through luck and ingenuity he was able to survive and eventually sneak into Iran, where he could make a subsistence, along with a number of other illegal workers, in construction. He was constantly in danger of deportation back to Pakistan, which happened more than once. Eventually he decided to try for a better life in the west and underwent a most harrowing and deadly journey over the mountains into Turkey. The description of this journey, in the hands of human traffickers, is graphic and disturbing. Finding Turkey inhospitable, he undertakes a water trip o Greece, accompanied by inept and unprepared fellow migrants. They barely survive, arriving soaked and in their underwear on the Greek coast. Luck again accompanies Mr. Akbari, and he lived to tell the tale to Mr. Geda. The story is valuable in getting a more direct sense of the desperation driving and the dangers endured by today's refugees. It is a remarkable story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15957190400644430803" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


