<span id="freeTextContainer3815903220283268829">Overall, a heartwarming tale about a young boy who escapes the conflicts of Afghanistan and makes his way across Europe, and to safety. The fact that this book is actually a true account of the life of Enaiatollah Akbari is even more staggering - such are the scale of some of the events that occur that it cannot surely be real? But it is. In spots, the text seems simplistic in its language and jumps through some events rapidly…but perhaps that is the point of it, as we hear Enaiatollah’s story t</span>
  <span id="freeText3815903220283268829" style="display:none">Overall, a heartwarming tale about a young boy who escapes the conflicts of Afghanistan and makes his way across Europe, and to safety. The fact that this book is actually a true account of the life of Enaiatollah Akbari is even more staggering - such are the scale of some of the events that occur that it cannot surely be real? But it is. In spots, the text seems simplistic in its language and jumps through some events rapidly…but perhaps that is the point of it, as we hear Enaiatollah’s story through his eyes and words.</span>
